Study of 1,500 teachers found 30 per cent have suffered online abuse by parents is on the rise accounting for 40 per cent of all reported insults this year . 
  Teachers’ union NASUWT said parents are using social media to intimidate staff . 
  One teacher said they had been called a ‘paedophile’ by a parent online . 
  Proportion of teachers suffering abuse from both parents and pupils has doubled to 60 per cent . 
 